<font face=Arial,Helvetica>
<b>California consumers fuming about electricity deregulation</b><br><font face=Arial,Helvetica size=1>Posted on  Friday, August 04 @ 01:27:26 EDT

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor=ffffff>
<font face=Arial,Helvetica>
<a href=search.php3?query=&topic=14&author=><img src=images/topics/economics.jpg border=0 Alt="Economic and Monetary Policy" align=right hspace=10 vspace=10></a>
<P>According to this <A href=http://washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A32955-2000Aug3.html>Washington Post story</A>, electricity deregulation is turning into a disaster in California.  Consumers' power bills have doubled and even tripled, rolling blackouts have hit San Francisco, and most of the state's power grid is operating in a state of emergency because of the shortage of power.</P>

<P>The story doesn't go into a great amount of detail.  Would any California readers care to give us some insight into what is going on there?</P> 
</td>
</tr>
